ksdk:manifest.name: SDK version 2.4.1 package for FRDM-KV11Z board
ksdk:manifest.brief: This is SDK version 2.4.1 manifest file. It describes the content of the SDK version 2.4.1 package for FRDM-KV11Z board and additional settings for tools that support SDK version 2.4.1

board.name: FRDM-KV11Z
board.description: FRDM-KV11Z: NXP速 Freedom Development Platform for Kinetis速 KV11 Family MCUs

specific.content: FRDM-KV11Z is a development platform for the Kinetis V series KV1x 64 KB and 128 KB MCU family built on the ARM速 Cortex速-M0+ processor.

device.name: MKV11Z7
device.description: KV1x: Kinetis KV1x-75 MHz, Entry-level 3ph FOC / Sensorless Motor Control MCUs based on ARM速 Cortex速-M0+

specific.content: The Kinetis速 KV1x MCU family is the entry point of the V series. Built upon the ARM速 Cortex速-M0+ core running at 75 MHz with hardware square root and divide capability, it delivers a 27% increase in performance in math-intensive applications versus comparable MCUs, allowing it to target BLDC as well as more computationally demanding PMSM motors. Additional features include integrated FlexCAN, dual 16-bit analog-to-digital controllers (ADCs) sampling at up to 1.2 mega samples per second (MS/s) in 12-bit mode, multiple motor control timers, up to 128 KB of flash memory and a comprehensive enablement suite from NXP速 and third-party resources, including reference designs, software libraries and motor configuration tools.
